ZZ80ASM(1)                 OpenBSD Reference Manual                 ZZ80ASM(1)

NNAAMMEE
     zzzz8800aassmm - z80 cross assembler

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
     zzzz8800aassmm [--dd _s_y_m_b_o_l _._._.] [--ff _b_|_m_|_h] [--l[_l_i_s_t_f_i_l_e]] [--oo _o_u_t_f_i_l_e] [--ss _a_|_n_|_u]
             [--vv] [--xx] _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e _._._.

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
     The zzzz8800aassmm utility assembles the files _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e _._._. and writes to the
     output file _o_u_t_f_i_l_e, and optionally the listing file _l_i_s_t_f_i_l_e_.

     The options are as follows:

     --dd _s_y_m_b_o_l _._._.
             Pre-define one or more _s_y_m_b_o_l_s with a value of zero.

     --ff _b_|_m_|_h
             Format _o_u_t_f_i_l_e as either binary, binary with Mostek header, or
             Intel Hex, respectively.  Intel Hex is the default format.

     --l[_l_i_s_t_f_i_l_e]
             Generate listing file as _l_i_s_t_f_i_l_e, or as _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e_._l_s_t by default.

     --oo _o_u_t_f_i_l_e
             Set output filename to _o_u_t_f_i_l_e instead of the default
             _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e_._b_i_n or _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e_._h_e_x.

     --ss _a_|_n_|_u
             Generate symbol table at end of listing file.  This option only
             works in combination with _-_l.  _a and _n sort the symbol table by
             address or name, respectively.  _u generates an unsorted table.

     --vv      Produce more verbose output.

     --xx      Do not output data into _o_u_t_f_i_l_e for DEFS in pass two of the
             assembler.

PPSSEEUUDDOO OOPPEERRAATTIIOONNSS
   SSyymmbbooll ddeeffiinniittiioonn aanndd mmeemmoorryy aallllooccaattiioonn::
           ORG <expression>
                       Set program address.

           <symbol> EQU <expression>
                       Define constant symbol.

           <symbol> DEFL <expression>
                       Define variable symbol.

           <symbol> DEFB <expression, 'char', ...>
                       Write 8 bit bytes in memory.

           <symbol> DEFW <expression, expression ...>
                       Write 16 bit words in memory.

           <symbol> DEFM <'string'>
                       Write character string in memory.

           <symbol> DEFS <expression>
                       Reserve space in memory.

   CCoonnddiittiioonnaall aasssseemmbbllyy::
           IFDEF <symbol>
                       Assemble if symbol defined.

           IFNDEF <symbol>
                       Assemble if symbol not defined.

           IFEQ <expression 1, expression 2>
                       Assemble if equal.

           IFNEQ <expression 1, expression 2>
                       Assemble if not equal.

           ELSE        Else clause for all conditionals.

           ENDIF       End of conditional assembly.

   MMaanniippuullaattiioonn ooff lliisstt ffiillee::
           TITLE <'string'>
                       Title for page header.

           PAGE <expression>
                       Number of lines per page.

           EJECT       Skip to new page.

           LIST        Turn listing on.

           NOLIST      Turn listing off.

   MMiisscceellllaanneeoouuss::
           INCLUDE <filename>
                       Include another source file.

           PRINT <'string'>
                       Print string to stdout in pass one of the assembler.

EEXXIITT SSTTAATTUUSS
     The zzzz8800aassmm utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.

AAUUTTHHOORRSS
     zzzz8800aassmm was written by Udo Munk <udo.munk@freenet.de> and updated by
     Chris Hettrick <chris@structfoo.com>.

